node.text: The eternally witty Tom Gauld is touring his new book, Department of Mind-Blowing Theories!! 🔭🔬🧲 He’ll be in Brooklyn, Chicago, LA, Portland, Toronto, Seattle, and Cambridge. . .  #sciencejokes #tomgauld #deptofmindblowingtheories #newbook #booklover #booklaunch #comics #scifi #drawnandquarterly

Who has as much fun as @elise_gravel ?? We’ll never know. This hilarious tale called The Worst Book Ever was published May 2019 👑 With impeccable comedic timing, it plays with conventional fairytale stories, turning them on their heads. It’s filled with silliness and laugh-out-loud fun, and works to break down the canonical status of the fairytales we all remember, one punch at a time. 🥊. .  #worstbookever #worstinstaever #worstpostever #kidsofinstagram #kidsbookstagram #bookstagram #readaloud

Yellow Yellow is the charmingly simple and beautifully drawn storybook by @mark_alan_stamaty 🌼Published May 2019, it depicts a bustling urban landscape wherein a young child finds adventure, play, and community. . . #kidsbooks #drawnandquarterly #enfant #readaloudrevival #childrensbooks #picturebookillustration #bookstagram #kidsbookstagram
Happy Valentine’s Day! ❤️😅😂❤️🤗❤️ Familiar Face by @michael.deforge is out in March.

Clyde Fans by Seth is next up! Published in April 2019, this masterful, epic comic peels back the optimism of mid-twentieth century capitalism. It has been celebrated by The New York Times, Comics Beat, The Guardian, The Washington Post, and more. .  #seth #drawnandquarterly #comics #graphicnovelswillsaveyourlife #graphicnovels #clydefans

It ain’t easy being a woman in science. Some of the hardships, as catalogued in Tom Gauld’s new book, out this April! #womeninscienceday #sciencejokes #mindblowingtheories #tomgauld #poodles #womeninscience

Ebony Flowers will be speaking with Taneka Stotts at Skylight Books in LA this month! She’ll also be attending the NAACP Image Awards ceremony ⭐️⭐️⭐️. .  @naacpimageawards #tanekastotts #skylightbooks #hotcomb #drawnandquarterly #comics #memoir #fiction

We’re incredibly excited to share that Michael DeForge will be touring Familiar Face!! 🙃🙂😉😌 He’ll be hitting up New York, Toronto, San Francisco, Los Angeles, and Minneapolis. Link to details in bio! Familiar Face is “a searing, surrealist critique of the culture of technological customization, and an ode to love in the face of overwhelming power.” - @publisherswkly #michaeldeforge #familiarface #drawnandquarterly #booktour

In April we also published the 7th instalment of our Eisner-nominated series Walt & Skeezix 1933-1934, created by Frank King. Designed and edited by Chris Ware, this classic comic finds the Gasoline Alley gang facing the turbulent depression years. #frankking #gasolinealley #waltandskeezix #drawnandquarterly #historicalcomics #chrisware

Credo: The Rose Wilder Lane Story by Peter Bagge is next in our round up! Published April 2019, this vivid comic tells the biography of writer, feminist, libertarian, and trailblazer Rose Wilder Lane! . .  #peterbagge #drawnandquarterly #rosewilderlane #historicalcomics #libertarian

Kitaro’s Yokai Battles by Shigeru Mizuki is next in our 2019 round up! Mizuki’s combination of intricate realism and equally evocative cartoons shines through in this manga from April 2019! . . .  #shigerumizuki #kitaro #yokaibattles #kitaroseries #drawnandquarterly #manga #mizukishigeru

Who hasn’t felt his pain? Next on our roundup of 2019 titles is Leaving Richard’s Valley by @michael.deforge! This surreal, engrossing book was released in April and has been a favourite around the world ❤️. .  #michaeldeforge #drawnandquarterly #computerproblems #friendship #loneliness #drawing #cartoonist

Up next in our 2019 roundup is This Woman’s Work by @juliedelporte_ . Published in March 2019, this stunning book examines feminism, and gender-based discrimination found in all tiers of society. It’s thoughtful, subtle, and incredibly courageous. #feminism #language #gender #drawing #comics #drawnandquarterly #feministlit

Late January is a great time to revisit our 2019 books and pick them up from your indie bookstore. Published in Feb 2019, James Sturm’s Off Season follows a couple through separation during the 2016 election #vote2020 #snowday #parenting #offseason #jamessturm #comics #drawnandquarterly

What an honour to meet Tian Veasna, author of Year of the Rabbit, and pictured here with translator Helge Dascher. This memoir retells his family’s experiences during the Khmer Rouge regime, offering a first person account of one of the 20th century’s greatest tragedies #khmerrouge #comics #witnessing #refugeestories #cambodia #tianveasna

A story about protest, endurance, and undying hope, The Hard Tomorrow by @squinkyelo reflects our time with sympathy and fidelity. 📢 . . .  #eleanordavis #hardtomorrow #protest #activism #feminism #home
Glenn Ganges in “I lay there and watched the one I love sleeping.” #glennganges #riveratnight #kevinhuizenga #sleeping #love #time #comics #drawnandquarterly

So lovely to see Hot Comb by Ebony Flowers, The River at Night by Kevin Huizenga, and Clyde Fans by Seth featured in the @guardian Review ❤️❤️❤️ . .  #ebonyflowers #kevinhuizenga #seth #guardian #bookstagram

Year of the Rabbit by Tian Veasna is out now!! “This is a vital piece of 20th century world history and a brilliant way to move towards understanding the world we live in now.” - D+Q Editor-in-Chief Tom Devlin. Read the whole blog post by Devlin, link in bio.  #yearoftherabbit #tianveasna
